post_text: Congratulations to Kyler Baird, Taylor Early, Emily Harmon, and Emma Shuman for all scoring Superior ratings at State Science Fair. Taylor was awarded a $2000 renewable scholarship to Ohio Northern University. Emma was awarded the top Veterinary Medicine Award, earning $250, and a second award of a week's scholarship to the Ohio State Stone Laboratory in Put-in-Bay. Their top performances earned Hicksville High School the Harold C. Shaw Outstanding School Award, one of only 14 schools in the state. Hicksville is so proud of our high achieving science students!

post_text: Due to the governor‚Äôs recent announcement and the school shutdown, the high school musical, Little Shop of Horrors, has been cancelled. We are so sad to deliver this news to you. We are discussing plans for a showcase in the fall or winter so that our students can perform some of the musical numbers. They have worked so hard, and we are so proud of them! We will keep you posted! To the seniors: We love you, and we will keep the musical memories with us forever. Thank you.

post_text: Four County Career Center is pleased to announce Kaitlyn Mallett from Hicksville High School as Student of the Month. Kaitlyn is the daughter of Cary and Kathy Mallett and is a senior in the Computer Programming and Game Design program at the Career Center. Kaitlyn was nominated by her instructor, Mr. Geiger. She is a member of Business Professionals of America, National Technical Honor Society, Student Council, and is on the Career Center Honor Roll. At Hicksville High School she is a member of the softball team. After Kaitlyn graduates, she plans to attend Northwest State Community College and major in computer programming.

Thanks for taking time out our your schedule to make the K-4 students SMILE!
